  <h1>2. Create the 11ty Template</h1>
  <p class="lead">Build a reusable static site template optimized for marketing websites.</p>

  <h2>Why 11ty?</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Fast:</strong> Generates static HTML — no server-side rendering</li>
    <li><strong>Simple:</strong> Uses familiar template languages (Nunjucks, Markdown)</li>
    <li><strong>Flexible:</strong> No framework lock-in</li>
    <li><strong>SEO-friendly:</strong> Clean HTML output, easy to optimize</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What to Tell Your Assistant</h2>
  <blockquote>
    "Create an 11ty starter template for marketing websites. Include a base layout, homepage, about page, contact page, and CSS with custom properties for easy theming."
  </blockquote>

  <p>Your assistant will create:</p>

  <h3>Project Structure</h3>
  <pre><code>├── src/
│   ├── _data/
│   │   └── site.json         # Site-wide config (name, URL, etc.)
│   ├── _includes/
│   │   └── layouts/
│   │       └── base.njk      # Base HTML template
│   ├── assets/
│   │   └── css/
│   │       └── style.css     # Styles with CSS variables
│   ├── pages/
│   │   ├── about.njk
│   │   └── contact.njk
│   └── index.njk             # Homepage
├── .eleventy.js              # 11ty configuration
├── amplify.yml               # AWS Amplify build settings
└── package.json</code></pre>

  <h2>Key Files</h2>

  <h3>Site Configuration (src/_data/site.json)</h3>
  <pre><code>{
  "name": "Your Site Name",
  "description": "Your site description",
  "url": "https://yourdomain.com"
}</code></pre>

  <h3>Amplify Build Config (amplify.yml)</h3>
  <pre><code>version: 1
frontend:
  phases:
    preBuild:
      commands:
        - npm ci
    build:
      commands:
        - npm run build
  artifacts:
    baseDirectory: _site
    files:
      - '**/*'
  cache:
    paths:
      - node_modules/**/*</code></pre>

  <h2>Push to GitHub</h2>
  <p>Once your assistant creates the template, tell them:</p>
  <blockquote>"Push this to the GitHub repo."</blockquote>

  <p>Your assistant will commit and push the code. You can verify at your repo URL.</p>

